Irish MMA fighter Conor McGregor @thenotoriousmma celebrated his wife's birthday a few days ago wearing his insane @jacobandco Astronomia ‘Baguette’ tourbillon in rose gold. 
The watch features a total of 342 invisibly set baguette-cut diamonds that adorn the dial’s backdrop, while 80 invisibly set, baguette-cut diamonds make up the lugs. Its four-arm movement rotates and floats through the sapphire and diamond-bound space of the completely see-through case. Limited edition of just 18 pieces with a list price of $1,000,000.00

To reach those goals you’ve got to be willing to play all the angles meticulously. From the relationship status between @JacobAndCo and Bugatti Rose gold and white diamonds baguette 💎🔥

The case is inspired by the flowing lines of the Chiron and the movement, or “engine block,” intended to duplicate the Bugatti engine, is placed under a massive sapphire crystal, on display for all to see. With the push of right-hand crown of the timepiece the engine comes to life, just like a true internal combustion engine. 
The movement is set with a total of 578 exquisite components. 
Right now Jacob’s workshop is doing something no one has ever even attempted before: to seamlessly combine engines and watches💯
